@dev The Migrations contract is a standard truffle contract that keeps track of which migrations were done on the current network.
 For yDai, we have updated it and added functionality that enables it as well to work as a deployed contract registry.
@dev Register a contract name and address
@dev Register the index of the last completed migration
@dev Copy the index of the last completed migration to a new version of the Migrations contract

devdoc.details: The Migrations contract is a standard truffle contract that keeps track of which migrations were done on the current network. For yDai, we have updated it and added functionality that enables it as well to work as a deployed contract registry.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

register(bytes32,address).details: Register a contract name and address

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setCompleted(uint256).details: Register the index of the last completed migration

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

upgrade(address).details: Copy the index of the last completed migration to a new version of the Migrations contract
